subject: Dear Beneficiary,
body:
Dear Beneficiary,
Please note that we have recovered the sum of $5,500,000.00 USD from
the Central Bank of West African States as abandoned inheritance funds
belonging to you.
We have programmed the $5,500,000.00 USD in an ATM Master Card so that
you can withdraw the money on your own in your country and advise you
to respond quickly to this message and follow the procedures to allow
us to send you the ATM Master Card without delay.
We will not hesitate to suspend this transaction and deposit the funds
into the African Union reserved account, if you delay in responding
and receiving the ATM Master Card.
Thanks,
Mr. Darlington Ozurumba.
Head of the European Commission.
Economic and Monetary Union (EMU) Nigeria.

subject: Re:   Dear Beneficiary,
body:
Hello Mr. Darlington Ozurumba,

Wow, this is such an unexpected surprise! I can't believe there was a sum of USD just sitting around in the Central Bank of West African States that belongs to me. I'm really curious about how you found out about this abandoned fund and why it was left unclaimed?

Also, could you please explain more about how the ATM Master Card works? How can I withdraw the money from it in my country? 

I'm looking forward to your response.

Best regards.

Best wishes,
Debra
